   <mods:titleInfo>
      <mods:title>[1849] December 20, Washington [City, D.C.] [to Adam Fergusson] / Andrew Ewing</mods:title>
   </mods:titleInfo>
   <mods:abstract>This is a letter from Andrew Ewing to Adam Fergusson, dated December 20, presumably in 1849. Ewing writes that the government is in great disorganization over the slavery question. He considers the Northern Democrats and Whigs to be anarchists. He also fears that the chaos in America might lead to an end of the liberty that America stands for.</mods:abstract>
